1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,433
你去菜市场买菜
You go to the market to buy vegetables

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:03,200
老板抓起一把青菜
The vendor grabs a handful of greens

3
00:00:03,366 --> 00:00:04,766
往电子秤上一放
Tosses them on the digital scale

4
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:06,566
屏幕跳出一个数字
A number pops up on the screen

5
00:00:06,833 --> 00:00:07,700
三块八
Three eighty

6
00:00:07,866 --> 00:00:08,900
你看一眼
You glance at it

7
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:09,900
扫码
Scan the code

8
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:10,800
走人
And leave

9
00:00:10,966 --> 00:00:13,166
整个过程可能不到十秒
The whole thing takes maybe ten seconds

10
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:14,566
但这十秒里
But in those ten seconds

11
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:17,400
藏着一个市场能不能运转的秘密
Lies the secret of whether a market can function

12
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:18,900
你没有亲手称
You didn't weigh it yourself

13
00:00:19,066 --> 00:00:20,400
你没有拆开秤看
You didn't take the scale apart

14
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,600
你甚至不知道这把秤准不准
You don't even know if the scale is accurate

15
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,100
可你还是付钱了
But you still paid

16
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:25,100
为什么
Why

17
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:27,366
因为你默认这杆秤是可信的
Because you assume the scale is trustworthy

18
00:00:27,466 --> 00:00:28,900
这件事太普通了
This is so ordinary

19
00:00:29,066 --> 00:00:31,800
普通到我们几乎忘了它有多重要
So ordinary we almost forget how important it is

20
00:00:31,966 --> 00:00:33,200
如果没有秤
Without a scale

21
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:36,233
每一次买菜，都会变成一次争吵
Every grocery run would turn into an argument

22
00:00:36,466 --> 00:00:37,533
老板说两斤
The vendor says two jin

23
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:39,200
你说最多一斤半
You say one and a half at most

24
00:00:39,366 --> 00:00:41,166
老板说我做生意讲良心
The vendor says I run an honest business

25
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,133
你说你这手是不是太重了
You say aren't you being a bit heavy-handed

26
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,700
一条鱼还没下锅
The fish hasn't even hit the pan yet

27
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:46,133
人先吵累了
But you're already exhausted from arguing

28
00:00:46,266 --> 00:00:49,166
所以一杆秤称的从来不只是重量
So a scale has never just weighed goods

29
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:50,566
它称的是信任
It weighs trust

30
00:00:50,666 --> 00:00:52,733
也称的是一个市场的脾气
And the temperament of a market

31
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:55,900
今天这条视频，我们就用一杆秤
Today's video uses a scale

32
00:00:55,966 --> 00:00:57,700
讲清楚三件事
To explain three things

33
00:00:57,966 --> 00:01:00,800
为什么市场最怕的不是贵，而是不准
Why markets fear inaccuracy more than high prices

34
00:01:00,966 --> 00:01:03,300
为什么中国古代要统一度量衡
Why ancient China unified weights and measures

35
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:06,266
以及今天的评分 信用 算法
And why today's ratings credit scores and algorithms

36
00:01:06,266 --> 00:01:07,700
为什么都是新的秤
Are all new kinds of scales

37
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:09,433
先想一个很小的场景
Picture a small scene first

38
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:10,966
你买一斤苹果
You buy a jin of apples

39
00:01:11,166 --> 00:01:12,800
老板说这一袋刚好一斤
The vendor says this bag is exactly one jin

40
00:01:12,966 --> 00:01:15,033
如果没有秤，你怎么办
Without a scale what do you do

41
00:01:15,233 --> 00:01:16,933
你只能凭感觉
You can only go by feel

42
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:17,966
你掂一掂
You heft it

43
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:19,166
他也掂一掂
He hefts it too

44
00:01:19,266 --> 00:01:20,566
你觉得轻了
You think it's light

45
00:01:20,766 --> 00:01:21,800
他觉得够了
He thinks it's enough

46
00:01:21,966 --> 00:01:23,400
这时候交易就卡住了
Now the transaction is stuck

47
00:01:23,566 --> 00:01:24,966
不是因为苹果不好吃
Not because the apples taste bad

48
00:01:25,166 --> 00:01:27,166
也不是因为价格谈不拢
Not because you can't agree on price

49
00:01:27,266 --> 00:01:29,900
而是因为双方没有一个共同承认的标准
But because neither side shares a recognized standard

50
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,800
经济学里有个词，叫交易成本
Economics has a term called transaction costs

51
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,766
说白了，就是一笔买卖还没完成之前
Simply put it's the time and energy spent

52
00:01:36,866 --> 00:01:39,766
你为了确认 讨价 怀疑 防骗
Before a deal closes verifying haggling doubting guarding against scams

53
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:41,633
花掉的时间和精力
All that effort you spend

54
00:01:41,766 --> 00:01:44,766
买菜的时候，你不想研究老板的人品
When buying groceries you don't want to vet the vendor's character

55
00:01:44,933 --> 00:01:47,766
老板也不想每卖一袋苹果都解释半天
The vendor doesn't want to explain himself every time either

56
00:01:47,933 --> 00:01:49,500
所以大家需要一杆秤
So everyone needs a scale

57
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:50,833
秤站在那里
The scale sits there

58
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,966
像一个不太说话的第三方
Like a quiet third party

59
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,500
它不替老板说话
It doesn't speak for the vendor

60
00:01:54,766 --> 00:01:55,800
也不替你说话
Or for you

61
00:01:55,933 --> 00:01:57,333
它只给一个数字
It just gives a number

62
00:01:57,433 --> 00:01:59,366
这个数字不一定让你开心
This number might not make you happy

63
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:01,600
但它让你们有办法继续交易
But it lets you keep transacting

64
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:03,500
这就是秤最厉害的地方
That's the scale's greatest power

65
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:06,433
它把一场可能发生的争吵
It takes a potential argument

66
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,400
压缩成了一个数字
And compresses it into a number

67
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,533
你会发现
You'll notice

68
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:12,500
生活里很多东西都在做同样的事
Many things in life do the same

69
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,466
餐厅菜单上的价格
Prices on a restaurant menu

70
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,066
快递单上的重量
Weight on a delivery slip

71
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:18,066
打车软件里的里程
Distance in a ride-hailing app

72
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:19,866
电表上的度数
Kilowatts on the meter

73
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,700
它们看起来只是数字
They look like just numbers

74
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:25,400
但这些数字的背后，都是在减少争吵
But behind each one is less arguing

75
00:02:25,566 --> 00:02:27,666
你不可能每天跟电力公司吵
You can't argue with the power company every day

76
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:29,700
说我家灯泡没开这么久
Saying my lights weren't on that long

77
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:32,466
你也不可能每次坐车都跟司机争
You can't fight with every driver over distance

78
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,500
说这段路没有五公里
Saying this ride wasn't five kilometers

79
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:36,400
如果没有共同标准
Without shared standards

80
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,133
生活会变得特别累
Life becomes exhausting

81
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:41,733
你会发现，市场不是靠热情运转的
Markets don't run on enthusiasm

82
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,000
市场是靠标准运转的
Markets run on standards

83
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,966
一旦标准不稳，人就开始互相猜
Once standards wobble people start guessing

84
00:02:47,133 --> 00:02:48,700
你猜老板有没有骗你
You guess if the vendor is cheating you

85
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:50,733
老板猜你是不是故意找茬
The vendor guesses if you're being difficult on purpose

86
00:02:50,966 --> 00:02:52,800
平台猜商家有没有刷单
Platforms guess if merchants are faking orders

87
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,966
用户猜评价是不是买来的
Users guess if reviews are bought

88
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:57,666
猜来猜去，交易就慢了
All this guessing slows everything down

89
00:02:57,833 --> 00:03:01,933
所以秤真正省下来的，不只是几毛钱
So what the scale really saves isn't just a few cents

90
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:04,900
而是人和人之间那点宝贵的耐心
It's that precious patience between people

91
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:08,700
很多时候，信任不是靠感动建立的
Often trust isn't built through moving moments

92
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:11,566
信任是靠一个大家都认的标准
Trust is built through a standard everyone accepts

93
00:03:11,700 --> 00:03:12,933
慢慢省出来的
Slowly accumulated over time

94
00:03:13,033 --> 00:03:14,966
你可能听过一句话
You may have heard this before

95
00:03:15,233 --> 00:03:16,866
秦始皇统一文字
Qin Shi Huang unified the writing system

96
00:03:17,033 --> 00:03:17,966
统一货币
Unified the currency

97
00:03:18,166 --> 00:03:19,300
统一度量衡
Unified weights and measures

98
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:20,800
前两个很好理解
The first two are easy to understand

99
00:03:20,966 --> 00:03:23,566
文字不统一，政令传不下去
Without unified writing decrees can't spread

100
00:03:23,766 --> 00:03:26,066
货币不统一，买卖做不顺
Without unified currency trade doesn't flow

101
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:28,400
但度量衡为什么也这么重要
But why are weights and measures equally important

102
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:30,966
这事儿如果只放在课本里看
If you only see this in a textbook

103
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,133
很容易变成一句背诵题
It's easy to treat it as a memorization question

104
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:36,266
你把它放到生意里，就立刻明白了
Put it in business and it clicks immediately

105
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,566
假设你是一个卖布的人
Say you're a cloth merchant

106
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:41,100
你从这个县买进一匹布
You buy a bolt of cloth in one county

107
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:43,000
到了另一个县再卖出去
And sell it in another

108
00:03:43,166 --> 00:03:44,166
问题来了
Here's the problem

109
00:03:44,366 --> 00:03:46,133
这边一尺是这么长
One chi here is this long

110
00:03:46,333 --> 00:03:48,266
那边一尺又是另一个长度
One chi there is a different length

111
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:50,100
这边一斤是这么重
One jin here weighs this much

112
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:51,666
那边一斤又差一点
One jin there is slightly different

113
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:55,000
你每走一个地方，都要重新换算一次
Every new place means recalculating

114
00:03:55,166 --> 00:03:57,000
你还得防着对方占便宜
You also have to guard against being shortchanged

115
00:03:57,233 --> 00:04:00,733
最后你会发现，赚钱不难，算账最累
Eventually you realize earning money isn't hard the accounting is exhausting

116
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,466
很多买卖不是做不成
Many deals don't fail

117
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,266
是被不统一的标准磨没了
They get ground down by inconsistent standards

118
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,333
统一度量衡做的
What unifying weights and measures did

119
00:04:07,366 --> 00:04:09,333
就是把这种麻烦先拿掉
Was remove this hassle upfront

120
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,200
你从 A 地买的东西
What you bought in place A

121
00:04:11,533 --> 00:04:13,266
到了 B 地还能被理解
Is still understood in place B

122
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,900
你在这个城市签的契约
A contract signed in one city

123
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:18,166
到了另一个城市还能执行
Can still be enforced in another

124
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:19,600
你卖的是一斤
You sell one jin

125
00:04:19,933 --> 00:04:22,866
别人听到一斤，知道你说的是什么
Others hear one jin and know what you mean

126
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,366
这看起来很朴素
This seems simple

127
00:04:24,566 --> 00:04:26,333
但它让市场变大了
But it made markets bigger

128
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:28,800
原来只能在熟人之间交易
Before you could only trade with people you knew

129
00:04:28,966 --> 00:04:30,766
后来可以跟陌生人交易
Later you could trade with strangers

130
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,800
原来只能在一个村里做买卖
Before you could only do business in one village

131
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:35,266
后来可以跨城 跨省 跨地区
Later across cities provinces and regions

132
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,800
一个市场真正变大的标志
The real sign of a market growing

133
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,366
不是人变聪明了
Isn't that people got smarter

134
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,966
而是陌生人之间也能放心交易
It's that strangers can trade with confidence

135
00:04:42,133 --> 00:04:44,900
秤 尺 斗 升，这些东西很小
Scales rulers measuring cups these are small things

136
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:47,066
但它们像一根根看不见的线
But they're like invisible threads

137
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:49,700
把很多陌生地方缝到了一起
Stitching unfamiliar places together

138
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:51,466
你今天网购也是这样
Online shopping today works the same way

139
00:04:51,566 --> 00:04:52,900
你没见过卖家
You've never met the seller

140
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,333
卖家也没见过你
The seller has never met you

141
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,333
你不知道仓库在哪里
You don't know where the warehouse is

142
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:58,066
你也不知道快递员是谁
You don't know who the courier is

143
00:04:58,166 --> 00:04:59,666
但你敢下单
But you still place the order

144
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,866
因为有标准
Because there are standards

145
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:02,166
商品规格
Product specifications

146
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:03,700
快递重量
Shipping weight

147
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:04,866
平台规则
Platform rules

148
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,266
售后流程
Return policies

149
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:07,333
支付记录
Payment records

150
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:10,466
这些东西加起来，就是今天的度量衡
All these together are today's weights and measures

151
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:13,300
没有它们，电商就不是电商
Without them e-commerce wouldn't be e-commerce

152
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:17,100
它会退回成一场大型讨价还价
It would regress into one giant bargaining session

153
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,266
你会每天问
You'd ask every day

154
00:05:18,366 --> 00:05:20,066
这件衣服到底多大
How big is this shirt really

155
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,466
这瓶东西到底多少毫升
How many milliliters are actually in this bottle

156
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:24,933
这个快递到底是不是少发了
Did this package really ship everything

157
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:27,166
你看，标准一旦消失
You see once standards disappear

158
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,966
信任就要靠人肉补上
Trust has to be filled in manually

159
00:05:29,166 --> 00:05:31,900
而人肉补信任，是最贵的
And manual trust is the most expensive kind

160
00:05:31,933 --> 00:05:34,566
菜市场里有一种场面，你应该见过
There's a scene at the market you've probably seen

161
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:38,166
东西卖贵了，顾客最多嘀咕两句
If something's overpriced customers grumble a bit

162
00:05:38,366 --> 00:05:39,700
下次不来了
And don't come back

163
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:41,733
但如果发现缺斤少两
But if they catch short-weighting

164
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,300
气氛马上就不一样
The mood shifts instantly

165
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:44,533
人会生气
People get angry

166
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:45,800
会拍视频
They film it

167
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:47,700
会喊旁边人来看
They call people over to see

168
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:48,800
为什么
Why

169
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,866
明明损失可能就几块钱
The loss might only be a few bucks

170
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,333
但那种火气，比单纯涨价大多了
But the anger is way bigger than from a price hike

171
00:05:54,433 --> 00:05:56,866
因为贵和骗，是两回事
Because expensive and cheated are two different things

172
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:59,100
贵，是你明码标价
Expensive means the price is clear

173
00:05:59,233 --> 00:06:00,366
我可以不买
I can choose not to buy

174
00:06:00,566 --> 00:06:03,566
骗，是你把选择权藏起来
Cheated means you hid my choice

175
00:06:03,633 --> 00:06:05,366
等我付完钱才发现不对
I only find out after paying

176
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:09,500
人对被骗的痛感，往往比对花钱更强
Being cheated hurts more than spending money

177
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:11,866
这也是为什么很多生意毁掉
That's why many businesses fail

178
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,400
不是因为价格高
Not because prices are high

179
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,566
而是因为用户觉得秤不准
But because users feel the scale is rigged

180
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,100
网约车绕路
Ride-hailing taking detours

181
00:06:17,366 --> 00:06:18,666
外卖分量缩水
Food delivery portions shrinking

182
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,733
会员规则藏得太深
Membership rules buried too deep

183
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:23,066
平台推荐看起来不透明
Platform recommendations feeling opaque

184
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:25,266
你不一定能说清楚哪里不对
You might not be able to articulate what's wrong

185
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:27,066
但你会有一种感觉
But you get a feeling

186
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,700
我好像被算计了
Like I've been played

187
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,766
这一下，信任就裂了
And just like that trust cracks

188
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:33,500
而信任一旦裂开，修起来很慢
Once cracked trust takes a long time to repair

189
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:34,800
商家可以打折
Merchants can offer discounts

190
00:06:34,966 --> 00:06:35,966
可以送券
Give coupons

191
00:06:36,233 --> 00:06:37,300
可以道歉
Apologize

192
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:40,466
但顾客心里那杆秤，已经偏了一次
But the customer's inner scale has already tilted once

193
00:06:40,633 --> 00:06:42,966
下次再买，他会多想一下
Next time they'll hesitate a moment longer

194
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:44,966
这一下，就是成本
That hesitation is the cost

195
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:47,300
你看很多老店为什么能活很久
Notice how many old shops survive so long

196
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:48,966
不一定是因为它最便宜
Not necessarily because they're cheapest

197
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,500
也不一定是因为它装修最好
Or because they have the best decor

198
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:55,000
而是你知道，它不会在秤上动手脚
But because you know they won't tamper with the scale

199
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:56,266
它可能话不多
They might not say much

200
00:06:56,533 --> 00:06:57,700
菜单也不花哨
The menu isn't fancy

201
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:00,100
但你坐下来，心里是稳的
But when you sit down you feel secure

202
00:07:00,233 --> 00:07:02,500
这种稳，就是品牌
That sense of security is a brand

203
00:07:02,766 --> 00:07:04,900
品牌不是广告里喊出来的
A brand isn't something shouted in ads

204
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,600
品牌是很多次小交易里
A brand is built through many small transactions

205
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:09,100
你没有被坑出来的
Where you weren't ripped off

206
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,900
一杆秤如果准，顾客不一定夸你
If the scale is accurate customers won't necessarily praise you

207
00:07:12,033 --> 00:07:15,366
但一杆秤如果不准，顾客一定记得你
But if it's not they'll definitely remember

208
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,500
所以真正会做生意的人
So people who truly know business

209
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,933
都会爱惜那杆看不见的秤
All cherish that invisible scale

210
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:21,366
它可能是价格表
It could be a price list

211
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,266
可能是退货规则
A return policy

212
00:07:23,433 --> 00:07:25,066
可能是客服承诺
A customer service promise

213
00:07:25,233 --> 00:07:28,000
也可能是你每次说到做到的习惯
Or your habit of always keeping your word

214
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:29,300
别小看这些东西
Don't underestimate these things

215
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:31,500
它们不一定马上让你赚钱
They might not make you money right away

216
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:34,500
但它们让别人愿意下一次还找你
But they make people want to come back next time

217
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:36,966
现在我们把那杆菜市场的秤
Now let's take that market scale

218
00:07:36,966 --> 00:07:38,066
搬到手机里
And move it into your phone

219
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,166
你点外卖，看评分
You order food and check ratings

220
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:42,500
你打车，看司机星级
You hail a ride and check the driver's stars

221
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,466
你住酒店，看评论
You book a hotel and read reviews

222
00:07:45,566 --> 00:07:47,900
你买东西，看销量和差评
You shop and check sales and negative reviews

223
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:50,900
你找工作，平台看你的履历
You job hunt and platforms check your resume

224
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:54,500
你申请贷款，系统看你的信用记录
You apply for a loan and systems check your credit

225
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:56,800
这些东西，都是秤
All of these are scales

226
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,333
只是它们称的不是重量
They just don't weigh physical weight

227
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,300
它们称的是可信度
They weigh trustworthiness

228
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,733
这听起来挺方便
Sounds pretty convenient

229
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:05,700
以前你要认识一个人，要靠熟人介绍
Before you needed personal introductions to know someone

230
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:08,866
现在一个评分 一串记录 一堆评论
Now a rating a record a bunch of reviews

231
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,566
就能帮你先判断一遍
Can help you judge first

232
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:13,066
它确实让很多交易变快了
It really has sped up many transactions

233
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:14,666
但问题也在这里
But the problem is also here

234
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,866
菜市场的秤，你还能看见
At the market you can at least see the scale

235
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:18,100
电子秤坏了
If the digital scale breaks

236
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:19,933
你至少知道自己怀疑什么
You at least know what to question

237
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:23,133
可手机里的秤，很多时候你看不见
But the scale in your phone is often invisible

238
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:25,766
平台为什么给这家店更多流量
Why does the platform give this shop more traffic

239
00:08:25,966 --> 00:08:28,500
算法为什么先推荐这个商品
Why does the algorithm recommend this product first

240
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,500
系统为什么觉得你风险高
Why does the system think you're high risk

241
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:32,866
AI 为什么给出这个判断
Why does AI make this judgment

242
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,566
你看到的是结果
You see the result

243
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,133
但你看不到它怎么称
But not how it weighed

244
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:37,666
这就带来一个新问题
This raises a new problem

245
00:08:37,933 --> 00:08:39,666
过去我们怕缺斤少两
Before we feared short weight

246
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,166
现在我们怕的是
Now we fear

247
00:08:41,366 --> 00:08:44,266
被一杆看不见的秤悄悄称完
Being silently weighed by an invisible scale

248
00:08:44,433 --> 00:08:45,966
你可能没有做错什么
You might not have done anything wrong

249
00:08:46,133 --> 00:08:49,266
但因为某些记录 标签 模型判断
But because of certain records tags or model judgments

250
00:08:49,566 --> 00:08:51,600
你被分到一个更贵的价格
You get assigned a higher price

251
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:53,300
一个更低的推荐
A lower recommendation

252
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,900
一个更差的机会
A worse opportunity

253
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,066
这不是科幻
This isn't sci-fi

254
00:08:56,166 --> 00:08:57,933
你日常已经在遇到了
You encounter it daily

255
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:59,133
同一个酒店
Same hotel

256
00:08:59,166 --> 00:09:01,566
不同账号看到的排序可能不一样
Different accounts see different rankings

257
00:09:01,766 --> 00:09:02,966
同一个商品
Same product

258
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:06,100
老用户和新用户拿到的优惠可能不一样
New and old users get different discounts

259
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:09,066
同一段内容，有的人被推荐
Same content gets recommended to some

260
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:12,000
有的人连被看见的机会都没有
While others don't even get a chance to be seen

261
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:15,300
这时候，问题就不只是秤准不准
Now the question isn't just whether the scale is accurate

262
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:18,600
还包括谁有权校准这杆秤
It's also who has the right to calibrate it

263
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:20,000
谁能解释它
Who can explain it

264
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:21,566
谁能申诉它
Who can appeal it

265
00:09:21,766 --> 00:09:25,466
谁能在它称错的时候，把数字改回来
Who can correct the number when it weighs wrong

266
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,466
对普通人来说，这里有三个小判断
For ordinary people here are three small guidelines

267
00:09:28,633 --> 00:09:32,033
第一，凡是关系到钱和机会的评分
First for any rating involving money or opportunities

268
00:09:32,033 --> 00:09:33,733
都不要只看一个平台
Don't rely on just one platform

269
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:36,333
多看一个来源，就是多一杆秤
One more source is one more scale

270
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:38,900
第二，遇到不透明的规则
Second when facing opaque rules

271
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,300
先别急着骂
Don't rush to curse

272
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,200
把截图 记录 时间留好
Save screenshots records and timestamps

273
00:09:42,366 --> 00:09:43,866
因为看不见的秤
Because invisible scales

274
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:46,300
最怕被具体证据照出来
Fear concrete evidence the most

275
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:48,933
第三，不要把自己的信用
Third don't stake your credit

276
00:09:48,966 --> 00:09:50,933
只押在一个入口上
On just one gateway

277
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,766
一个账号 一个平台 一个模型
One account one platform one model

278
00:09:52,766 --> 00:09:54,700
不能决定你全部的价值
Cannot determine your full worth

279
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,366
你要给自己留几杆备用的秤
Keep a few backup scales for yourself

280
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,966
作品是一杆秤
Your portfolio is a scale

281
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:01,266
客户反馈是一杆秤
Client feedback is a scale

282
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:02,900
朋友推荐是一杆秤
Friend referrals are a scale

283
00:10:03,133 --> 00:10:05,966
长期稳定的交付，也是一杆秤
Consistent long-term delivery is also a scale

284
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,333
最后回到菜市场
Finally back to the market

285
00:10:07,566 --> 00:10:11,000
那杆秤放在摊位上，很安静
The scale sits on the stall very quiet

286
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:14,200
你付钱的时候，可能连看都没认真看
When you pay you might not even look closely

287
00:10:14,366 --> 00:10:15,700
但只要它不准
But if it's inaccurate

288
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:18,100
一条街的信任都会跟着晃一下
The trust of a whole street wavers

289
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:21,300
市场不是靠大家都善良才运转
Markets don't run because everyone is kind

290
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:24,533
市场是靠大家都有一杆愿意承认的秤
Markets run because everyone accepts a common scale

291
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:26,733
下次你看到秤上的数字
Next time you see a number on a scale

292
00:10:26,966 --> 00:10:28,300
可以多停一秒
Pause for an extra second

293
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:30,366
它称出来的不是一斤苹果
It's not weighing a jin of apples

294
00:10:30,566 --> 00:10:32,933
是你愿不愿意相信眼前这个人
It's weighing whether you're willing to trust the person in front of you

295
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,633
也是这个世界
And whether this world

296
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:37,200
愿不愿意把买卖做得轻松一点
Is willing to make trade a little easier
